Cf. Quint. IV 1, 1 (cited below) 723 2, 26. Aper does not condemn this practice, and it is expressly recommended by Quint. (cf. IV 2 VII 10, 12 IX 2, 17 etc), but he objects to what seem to him excessively long intro- ductions of this kind, tolerated by the audiences of the Republic. Cf. Quint.
